main event: A possible sighting of a satellite (Echo II) over Nauvoo, Illinois on June 23, 1967.
interesting points: The report describes an object that was observed for 7 minutes, moving in a south direction.
The observer was in a tent when they saw the object.
The observer was unable to estimate the speed or distance of the object.
The object was described as a metallic blue object that vanished like a 'diving light'.
A sketch was provided showing the object as seen through a 100 powered telescope.
